omment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#D5D4D5><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uuzzelterror.showPublicProfile?language=EN>UzzelTerror</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>8/28/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000033>12:19:37 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">The coming of an Erudite Shadow Knight</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Uzzel Terrorspawn was originally born Ultiz Magicleap, born to two powerful mages, living in a hut not far from Kerra Isle. At an early age, his parents made sure that his destiny was clear; He would follow in his parents’ glory as a mage.<br>
<br>
The problem was that Ultiz, now Uzzel, was not as intelligent or as adept at the mage arts as his parents. Uzzel was stubborn and did not keep to the practices, favoring the might of the sword. His parents were outraged. Ridiculed by his parents and other children, he led a life taunted and laughed at. Until one day, he brought his sword to study and began taunting the young magic users with courage and arrogance unseen before. Push led to shove, and Uzzel, lifting the heavy bastard sword he found high above his head, cleaved an aspiring enchanter, slicing almost through this enchanter’s body, killing him instantly. He saw the fear in the enchanter’s eyes and felt a rush unlike any he had ever felt. Upon returning home, he told his father of his deed, looking for his approval, instead he found horror in his father’s face. They quickly journeyed south in an attempt to save the son they still loved and had faith would outgrow this bloodlust. They were wrong.<br>
<br>
Uzzel continued to ignore his magic teachings in favor for the sword. He enjoyed watching the fear of the small animals and kobolds and how they reacted to that fear. He harnessed his own fear to turn it into a mighty force within him.  It was then that his parents lost hope and left him one day, with five days of food and water and no word of return. Uzzel’s arrogance had grown to the point that he did not care. He never saw his parents again. He changed his name and made further south.<br>
<br>
Tired and hungry, he traveled to the tip of the coast only to find deserted rock and what seemed to be, a bottomless pit. This is the day his God would find him. He watched as an Erudite in blackened robes walked to a rock and began to search. Desperate and tired, Uzzel attacked him, using his own fear to attempt to scare the robed Erudite into submission. Such was not the case. The Erudite smiled and Uzzel felt very weak, as if all his energy was sapped from him. From nowhere, a skeleton sprung from the shadows, pummeling Uzzel to an inch of his life. The last thing he heard was “Calm, my pet”.<br>
<br>
When he woke, he was standing in a great hall, armored Erudites all around him. At his feet, laid a tattered tunic and rusted blade. Then he heard a voice speak:<br>
<br>
“Go to the world, Child of Cazic-Thule. Spread your fear, if you live, perhaps I will teach you the true power of Fear, worthless cur!”<br>
<br>
And that he did, he traveled the ocean, the swamp, desert, and towns along the way, making few friends, letting his greed and power grow, learning what he could, when he could. He immersed himself in the Dark Arts, but he only cared about those Arts that enhanced his melee skill. But he traveled alone…<br>
<br>
In his travels of the Estate of Unrest, since he decided to learn about the Dark Arts, by combating the Dark Arts, he came across a Darkened Elf with poers similiar to his own and an Ogre who wielded ancient and crude magicks. He was invited to join the ranks of this band and found the powers of others useful as well. Uzzel swallowed his pride and began his travels with the Ebon Tear.<br>
<br>
